==English==

===Etymology===
From {{G.}} ''[[Ästhetik]]'' or {{F.}} ''[[esthétique]]'', both from {{Gr.}} ''[[αισθητική]]'' ("a perceiver", "a sensitive person").

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-aesthetic.ogg|Audio (US)}}
:* {{rhymes|ɛtɪk}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Concerned with [[beauty]], [[artistic]] impact, or [[appearance]].
#: ''It works well enough, but the shabby exterior offends his '''aesthetic''' sensibilities.''

